'''Ivan Bašić''' ({{IPA|hr|ǐʋan bǎʃitɕ|pron}}; born 30 April 2002) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Kazakhstan Premier League]] club [[FC Astana|Astana]]. Born in Croatia, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Bašić started his professional career at [[HŠK Zrinjski Mostar|Zrinjski Mostar]], before joining [[FC Orenburg|Orenburg]] in 2022. Three years later, he signed with Astana.

A former youth international for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bašić made his senior international debut in 2023, earning 17 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Early career===
Bašić started playing football at [[HŠK Posušje|Posušje]], before joining [[HŠK Zrinjski Mostar|Zrinjski Mostar's youth academy]] in 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/ivan-basic-potpisao-prvi-ugovor-s-hsk-zrinjski/190409111|title=Ivan Bašić potpisao prvi ugovor s HŠK Zrinjski|website=klix.ba|date=9 April 2019|access-date=12 April 2019|language=bs}}</ref> He made his professional debut against [[FK Sloboda Tuzla|Sloboda Tuzla]] on 22 August 2020 at the age of 18.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/zrinjski-se-ponovo-mucio-s-realizacijom-ali-gol-talentovanog-masica-bio-je-dovoljan/372841|title=Zrinjski se ponovo mučio s realizacijom, ali gol talentovanog Mašića bio je dovoljan|website=sportsport.ba|date=22 August 2020|access-date=24 August 2020|language=bs}}</ref> On 16 May 2021, he scored his first professional goal in a triumph over [[FK Krupa|Krupa]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/zrinjski-bez-problema-do-pobjede-protiv-krupe/399198|title=Zrinjski bez problema do pobjede protiv Krupe|website=sportsport.ba|date=16 May 2021|access-date=16 May 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

===Orenburg===
In June 2022, Bašić was transferred to Russian side [[FC Orenburg|Orenburg]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/jedan-od-najboljih-igraca-napustio-zrinjski-karijeru-nastavlja-u-rusiji/127919|title=Jedan od najboljih igrača napustio Zrinjski, karijeru nastavlja u Rusiji|website=faktor.ba|date=24 June 2022|access-date=24 June 2022|language=bs}}</ref> He made his official debut for the team on 16 July against [[PFC Krylia Sovetov Samara|Krylia Sovetov]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/basic-upisao-asistenciju-u-zvanicnom-debiju-u-rusiji/430016|title=Bašić upisao asistenciju u zvaničnom debiju u Rusiji|website=sportsport.ba|date=17 July 2022|access-date=17 July 2022|language=bs}}</ref> On 31 July, he scored his first goal for Orenburg against [[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/366389-u21-reprezentativac-bih-zabio-lijep-gol-u-rusiji|title=U21 reprezentativac BiH zabio lijep gol u Rusiji|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=31 July 2022|access-date=1 August 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

===Astana===
In July 2025, Bašić moved to Kazakh outfit [[FC Astana|Astana]] on a contract until December 2026.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/iznenadjujuci-transfer-zmaj-nakon-tri-godine-napustio-rusiju-i-otisao-u-kazahstan/595889|title=Iznenađujući transfer: Zmaj nakon tri godine napustio Rusiju i otišao u Kazahstan|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=2 July 2025|access-date=2 July 2025|language=bs}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for the squad against [[FC Zhetysu|Zhetysu]] on 6 July.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/ivan-basic-upisao-debi-u-novom-timu|title=Ivan Bašić upisao debi u novom timu|website=n1info.ba|date=6 July 2025|access-date=8 July 2025|language=bs}}</ref> On 24 July, he scored his first goal for Astana in a [[2025–26 UEFA Conference League#Second qualifying round|UEFA Conference League qualifier]] against [[FC Zimbru Chișinău|Zimbru Chișinău]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/ivan-basic-spasio-astanu-bh-reprezentativac-pogodio-za-izjednacenje-protiv-zimbrua/250724152|title=Ivan Bašić spasio Astanu, bh. reprezentativac pogodio za izjednačenje protiv Zimbrua|website=klix.ba|date=24 July 2025|access-date=24 July 2025|language=bs}}</ref> Seven months later, he scored his first league goal in a defeat of [[FC Tobol|Tobol]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/504598-ivan-basic-pogodio-u-pobjedi-astane|title=Ivan Bašić pogodio u pobjedi Astane|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=20 March 2026|access-date=20 March 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Bašić represented [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at various youth levels. He also served as a [[Captain (association football)|captain]] of the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-21 football team|under-21 team]] under coach Igor Janković.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/kapiten-mlade-reprezentacije-bih-na-korak-sam-od-prve-ekipe-ne-zelim-igrati-za-rusiju|title=Kapiten mlade reprezentacije BiH: Na korak sam od prve ekipe, ne želim igrati za Rusiju|website=n1info.ba|date=7 November 2023|access-date=8 November 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

In September 2023, he received his first senior call up, for [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group J|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifiers]] against [[Liechtenstein national football team|Liechtenstein]] and [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/prva-izjava-save-milosevica-nakon-imenovanja-vjerujem-u-ovu-reprezentaciju-nova-imena-na-spisku/514760|title=Prva izjava Save Miloševića nakon imenovanja: Vjerujem u ovu reprezentaciju, nova imena na spisku|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=29 September 2023|access-date=1 October 2023|language=bs}}</ref> but had to wait until 19 November to make his debut against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/reprezentacija/sedmi-poraz-za-kraj-najlosijih-kvalifikacija-u-historiji-reprezentacije-bih-909091|title=Sedmi poraz za kraj najlošijih kvalifikacija u historiji reprezentacije BiH|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=19 November 2023|access-date=20 November 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Bašić was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

